File Structure:

index.html — The skeleton of the whole game. It sets up two "screens": the main menu div (#mainMenu) and the game container div 
(#game-container). It loads all the external scripts (Phaser library, your JS files, the Google Font), 
and links the CSS. It's basically the glue that holds everything together in the browser.

style.css — Yes, this is only for the main menu and the HTML UI. It styles the main menu background, the title text, the buttons,
layout centering, fonts, etc. Once you click Play and Phaser takes over, CSS has zero control — Phaser renders everything on a
<canvas> element with its own internal rendering engine. So any in-game visuals (HUD, enemies, platforms, buttons) 
are all drawn by Phaser, not CSS.

script.js — This handles the main menu logic only. Things like button click handlers for Play, maybe difficulty selection,
showing/hiding the menu, and calling startGame() which is defined in main.js. It's the bridge between the HTML menu and 
the Phaser game.

main.js — This is the entire game. Everything Phaser-related lives here: the GameScene class which contains preload()
(loads/generates all assets), create() (builds the level — ground, platforms, enemies, coins, player, HUD, colliders), 
and update() (runs every frame — movement, shooting, input). It also has all the game logic like hitPlayer(), 
checkLevelComplete(), showGameOver(), showLevelComplete(), showGameWin(), and the Phaser game config at the bottom. 
This is the file we've been fixing.

index.html + style.css + script.js are all just the front door (main menu). main.js is the actual game.